text: Eileen Grubba is an American film and television actress born in Anchorage, Alaska. As a child, she overcame a deadly virus contracted from a vaccine that paralyzed her from the waist down, she recovered, and then beat cancer. She is now an advocate for performers with disabilities and families with genetic cancers.
